snippet.title: Sam‡§¨‡§π‡§æ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞ - Official Trailer | Vicky Kaushal | Meghna Gulzar | Ronnie S | In Cinemas 01.12.2023
snippet.description:
To the Indian army, to the nation and its people, we present to you a glimpse into the life of India's Greatest Soldier, Sam Manekshaw. 

#SamBahadur Trailer Out Now! 
#Sam‡§¨‡§π‡§æ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞ in cinemas 1.12.2023

#SamIsHere 

Sam‡§¨‡§π‡§æ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞ is a tribute to Field Marshal Sam HFJ Manekshaw, MC, India's first Field Marshal and a legendary Army General. His career witnessed the shaping of India's geopolitical borders, and his life was marked by significant milestones, from fighting in World War II to being the Chief of Army Staff during the 1971 Indo-Pakistan war, that led to the creation of Bangladesh.
This RSVP film explores his dynamic personality and his unparalleled military career, offering a glimpse into the life of a no-nonsense Army Commander, also known as "Sam Bahadur" by the soldiers he led.

snippet.title: IND Beat SA: Kohli's Triple Blast, Shoaib Akhtar Shocked! | Aakash Chopra Reaction | World Cup 2023
snippet.description:
India Beats South Africa World Cup 2023 Live Updates: In the match played between India and South Africa in the World Cup 2023, India has defeated South Africa. Batting first, Team India had given a target of 327 runs to South Africa to win. In response to which South African team was out within 100 runs. Kohli played a century for India. Shreyas Iyer played an inning of 77 runs. On the bowling front, Ravindra Jadeja took 5 wickets and Kuldeep took 2 wickets. The entire South African team could score only 83 runs. The 243-run victory, which came on the occasion of Virat Kohli's birthday, was spectacular.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

Today‚Äôs recipe is Diwali faral shankarpali using 1 kilo maida. It turns out nice, crispy and flaky. Diwali faral is incomplete without shankarpali. We already have seen different recipes if shankarpali. This is full proof recipe the proportion used is just perfect. It is a very easy and simple recipe. You can make it within no time. Besides, I am sharing few tips to make perfect shankarpali. This is a popular Marathi recipe. Also it can be a good tea time snack. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Milk
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Sugar
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Ghee
‚Ä¢ 7 cups / 1 kilo Maida
‚Ä¢ Oil for frying

Method:
‚Ä¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and add milk and sugar. 
‚Ä¢ Heat it up together until sugar is dissolved. 
‚Ä¢ When sugar is dissolved and the mixture begins to boil, turn off the gas and add ghee. 
‚Ä¢ Melt ghee before measuring. Make sure you don‚Äôt use thick ghee. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and base for shankarpali is ready. 
‚Ä¢ Transfer the base into the maida and mix in with the help of ladle. 
‚Ä¢ Knead the mixture into dough. 
‚Ä¢ Make small portions of the dough. Keep the leftover dough covered with a wet cloth.
‚Ä¢ Take one portion and roll it into a thick chapati. The thickness of the chapati should be about 1 
  cm. 
‚Ä¢ Cut off the edges and roll the chapati little more if you want. 
‚Ä¢ Cut shankarpali into size and shape you want and take them out into a dish. 
‚Ä¢ Rolled out shankarpali should not dry out. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil on high heat for about 5 minutes and reduce the heat to low. 
‚Ä¢ Drop shankarpali into hot oil and fry it well for at least 3-4 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ If oil is hot enough and still shankarpali dissolves in oil, then add a little more maida into the 
  dough. Add a little milk and knead the dough again. Roll out shankarpali and fry. It won‚Äôt dissolve. 
‚Ä¢ When shankarpali gets nice golden color from all sides, take it out, drain excess oil and transfer it 
  into a dish. Shankarpali is ready.
‚Ä¢ You can store them in an air tight container when they cool down completely. They have shelf life 
  of about 1 month.

‚Ä¢ Melt ghee before measuring. Make sure you don‚Äôt use thick ghee. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and base for shankarpali is ready. 
‚Ä¢ Transfer the base into the maida and mix in with the help of ladle. 
‚Ä¢ Knead the mixture into dough. 
‚Ä¢ Make small portions of the dough. Keep the leftover dough covered with a wet cloth.
‚Ä¢ Take one portion and roll it into a thick chapati. The thickness of the chapati should be about 1 
  cm. 
‚Ä¢ Cut off the edges and roll the chapati little more if you want. 
‚Ä¢ Cut shankarpali into size and shape you want and take them out into a dish. 
‚Ä¢ Rolled out shankarpali should not dry out. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil on high heat for about 5 minutes and reduce the heat to low. 
‚Ä¢ Drop shankarpali into hot oil and fry it well for at least 3-4 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ If oil is hot enough and still shankarpali dissolves in oil, then add a little more maida into the 
  dough. Add a little milk and knead the dough again. Roll out shankarpali and fry. It won‚Äôt dissolve. 
‚Ä¢ When shankarpali gets nice golden color from all sides, take it out, drain excess oil and transfer it 
  into a dish. Shankarpali is ready.
‚Ä¢ You can store them in an air tight container when they cool down completely. They have shelf life 
  of about 1 month.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbour. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Raj Anankat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or be prepared to leave the premises.

snippet.title: NEW! Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah | Ep 3922 | 7 Nov 2023 | Teaser
snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to SAB: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Episode 3922: Jetha Ka Zabardast Surprise
--------------------------------------------------------
Bagha and Nattu Kakka persuade Jetha that he should have a small get-together as he is going to announce a big surprise for Babita. Jethalal invites everyone to the clubhouse in the evening and tells Babita he has a huge surprise in store for her. He also keeps pizza and ice cream in the clubhouse for the society members. When everyone learns of Jethalal's surprise, how will they all respond? Watch the episode to find out what happens 

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

A sensible and ambitious journalist joins a media company run by a suave maverick man. What will happen when she starts falling in love with him despite the red flags? 'Barsatein - Mausam Pyaar Ka' stars Shivangi Joshi and Kushal Tandon in lead roles.

snippet.description:

Mannat Murad Episode 12 - [Eng Sub] - Iqra Aziz - Talha Chahour - Digitally Presented by PEL - 6th November 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Mannat Murad Digitally Presented by PEL

Mannat is a beautiful young girl who hails from a progressive family that values love, care, and mutual respect. Raised in an environment where everyone's choices are respected, Mannat enjoys the freedom to make her own decisions. Following the untimely demise of her parents, she finds support from her elder brother, Nafees, who showers her with affection.

On the other hand, Murad belongs to a conservative family where his mother, the matriarch, wields significant influence over his life choices. As the only son, Murad is burdened with the responsibility of fulfilling his family's expectations. Soft-spoken and romantic by nature, Murad finds himself unable to defy his mother's authority, especially after the passing of his father.

Despite their starkly contrasting backgrounds, Mannat and Murad's hearts find solace in each other's presence, and they fall deeply in love. However, their families' interference creates misunderstandings between Mannat and Murad, testing the strength of their bond.

Will their families agree to their union? Will Mannat's family, with their open-mindedness, find common ground with Murad's conservative household? Can Mannat and Murad's love for each other withstand the motives of their families, who seek to create further misunderstandings between them?

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

#chakalirecipe #madhurasrecipe #bhajnichakli

Ingredients:
Bhajani
‚Ä¢ 2 1/2 cup / 500 gm Rice
‚Ä¢ 1 cup / 200 gm Chana dal
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Moong dal
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Urad dal
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup / 100 gm Poha
‚Ä¢ 20 gm Coriander seeds
‚Ä¢ 20 gm Cumin seeds
Chakali
‚Ä¢ 3 cups Water
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Oil
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Oil
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Coriander powder
‚Ä¢ 1 kilo Chakali bhajani
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Ajwain / Carom seeds
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp white Sesame seeds
‚Ä¢ Oil for frying

Method:
‚Ä¢ Wipe the rice really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
‚Ä¢ Wipe chana dal really good with clean wet cotton cloth. 
‚Ä¢ Wipe moong dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
‚Ä¢ Wipe urad dal really good with a clean wet cotton cloth. 
‚Ä¢ You can wash and dry all these ingredients if you want. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and roast rice really good. 
‚Ä¢ The rice should be roasted well but the color should not change. 
‚Ä¢ When the rice is roasted well take it out into a dish. 
‚Ä¢ In the same pan roast chana dal really good until it begins to get reddish color and take it out into 
  a dish. 
‚Ä¢ In the same pan roast moong dal well until it gets reddish color and take it out into a dish. 
‚Ä¢ In the same pan roast urad dal really good until it gets light golden color and take it out into a 
  dish. 
‚Ä¢ Roast poha really good and transfer them into the dish. 
‚Ä¢ In the same pan roast coriander seeds and cumin seeds together on low heat until nice aroma 
  begins to release from it and transfer it into the dish. 
‚Ä¢ Mix everything well together and let it cool down. 
‚Ä¢ Grind it from the mill. Make sure that it is ground after rice or jawar is ground and not after wheat. 
‚Ä¢ Blend it into flour in mixer and sieve it through flour strainer. 
‚Ä¢ Blend the leftover coarse flour in the strain again in blender and sieve it. Bhajani for chakali is 
  ready.
Chakali
‚Ä¢ Heat up water in a pan and add oil. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and add red chili powder, salt, coriander powder. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and when the mixture boils really good, reduce the heat to low. 
‚Ä¢ Add the bhajani flour and turn off the gas. 
‚Ä¢ Add carom seeds, sesame seeds and mix everything well together quickly. 
‚Ä¢ Transfer the ukad into a dish and knead dough. If needed use very little hot water. 
‚Ä¢ Knead the ukad really good when it is still hot. The consistency of the dough should be stiff. 
‚Ä¢ Take small portion from the dough and knead it really good again. 
‚Ä¢ Make a smooth and even roll and transfer it into chakali machine. 
‚Ä¢ Press the dough well and roll out chakali from it on a butter paper. 
‚Ä¢ Seal both the ends of the chakali really good. 
‚Ä¢You can use plastic sheet or dish in place of butter paper. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil in a pan on medium to high heat for about 6-7 minutes and drop a small chakali in it. 
‚Ä¢ If it is fried well, then the oil is hot enough. 
‚Ä¢ Drop chakali into hot oil and fry well. 
‚Ä¢ When the chakali begins to settle at the bottom, flip it over and fry well from other side too. 
‚Ä¢ When chakali begins to settle at the bottom of the pan, it means it is fried well from both sides. 
‚Ä¢ Take the chakali out, drain excess oil and transfer it into a dish. Chakali is ready.

Mannat Murad Digitally Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream

Mannat is a beautiful young girl who hails from a progressive family that values love, care, and mutual respect. Raised in an environment where everyone's choices are respected, Mannat enjoys the freedom to make her own decisions. Following the untimely demise of her parents, she finds support from her elder brother, Nafees, who showers her with affection.

On the other hand, Murad belongs to a conservative family where his mother, the matriarch, wields significant influence over his life choices. As the only son, Murad is burdened with the responsibility of fulfilling his family's expectations. Soft-spoken and romantic by nature, Murad finds himself unable to defy his mother's authority, especially after the passing of his father.

To make Besan Aata 

 ‚Ä¢ Saute chana dal for 10 to 12 minutes till it changes in light golden colour. 
 ‚Ä¢ After cooling grind all. 

Besan Ladu Recipe 

 ‚Ä¢ On low heat, Saute chana dal to the kadhai.  
 ‚Ä¢ After 2 to 3 minutes, add remaining ghee and saute for 20 to 22 minutes till its get light golden colour. 

 ‚Ä¢ After 20 minutes, sprinkle 2 tsp of water / milk, saute for 2 minutes and let them cool down. 
 ‚Ä¢ After cooling add sugar powder, cardamom powder, bedane and make all the ladu.
